GDD - Survival Game (Game Design Document - Survival Game)

This is a top-down survival game where the player must gather resources, 
build shelter, 
and fend off enemies to survive in a hostile environment. 
The game features a dynamic day-night cycle, weather effects, and a variety of crafting options.

Project Link: https://github.com/DamrongS/GDD---Survival-Game
GDD Link: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IJ2C_lnbNUXAmIutAs58g1jQfUIbfmxFuaQ2LBYkUAE/edit?usp=sharing

Optimizations:
In this project, i am always trying to go for the OOP approach, and i am using the component-based design pattern to make my code more modular and reusable. 
I also implemented a simple object pooling system for the enemies to improve performance and reduce memory usage.
This allows me to reuse enemy objects instead of creating and destroying them frequently, which can lead to performance issues.

Lessons Learned:
1. The importance of planning and designing before coding. 
   By creating a detailed game design document, I was able to have a clear vision of the game mechanics, features, and overall structure before starting development.